definition.value: A member of the class of hexadecen-1-ols that is hexadecanol containing a double bond located at position 9 (the Z-geoisomer).
A wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of hexadecen-1-ol with  oleic acid.
A wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of oleic acid with stearyl alcohol.
A wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of oleic acid and oleyl alcohol.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is icosane in which one of the terminal methyl hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of icosan-1-ol with oleic acid.
A wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of  hexadecan-1-ol with  palmitoleic acid.
An N-acylglycine having nicotinoyl as the acyl substituent.

A proanthocyanidin consisting of two molecules of (+)-catechin joined by a bond between positions 4 and 8' in alpha-configuration. It can be found in red wine, in barley, in beer, in peach or in Jatropha macrantha, the Huanarpo Macho.
A  wax ester obtained by the formal condensation of palmityl alcohol with stearic acid.

A proanthocyanidin consisting of two molecules of (-)-epicatechin joined by a bond between positions 4 and 8' in a beta-configuration. Procyanidin B2 can be found in Cinchona pubescens (Chinchona, in the rind, bark and cortex), in Cinnamomum verum (Ceylon cinnamon, in the rind, bark and cortex), in Crataegus monogyna (Common hawthorn, in the flower and blossom), in Uncaria guianensis (Cat's claw, in the root), in Vitis vinifera (Common grape vine, in the leaf), in Litchi chinensis (litchi, in the pericarp), in the apple, in Ecdysanthera utilis and in red wine.

A proanthocyanidin consisting of (-)-epicatechin and (+)-catechin units joined by a bond between positions 4 and 8' respectively  in a beta-configuration.. Procyanidin B1 can be found in Cinnamomum verum (Ceylon cinnamon, in the rind, bark or cortex), in Uncaria guianensis (cat's claw, in the root), and in Vitis vinifera (common grape vine, in the leaf) or in peach.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of L-erythro-3-methylmalyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of mesaconyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of 3-methylfumaroyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of (3R)-citramalyl-CoA.
An  organosulfate oxoanion obtained by the deprotonation of the sulfo group of  holothurin A3 acid.
A triterpenoid saponin that is a  tetrasaccharide derivative of 3,12,17,25-tetrahydroxy-18,20-epoxylanost-9(11)-ene-18,22-dione.
A organosulfate oxoanion obtained by the deprotonation of the sulfo group of holothurin A4 acid.
A triterpenoid saponin that is a tetrasaccharide derivative of 3,12,17,24-tetrahydroxy-18,20-epoxylanost-9(11)-en-18-one.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of two (-)-epicatechin and one (+)-catechin units joined in sequence by (4beta->8)- and (4beta->6)-linkages.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of three (-)-epicatechin units joined by two successive (4beta->8)-linkages.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of three (+)-catechin trimer joined by two successive (4alpha->8)-linkages.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as palmitoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) where the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3'R)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B2.
Azobenzene substituted at the phenyl 4-positions by an amino and a nitro group.
A nucleotide residue derived from  5-(2-methoxy-2-oxoethyl)uridine 5'-monophosphate.
A uridine 5'-phosphate that is the 5-(2-methoxy-2-oxoethyl) derivative of uridine 5'-monophosphate.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3R)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B1.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3R)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B2.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3'S)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B1.
Uridine bearing an additional carboxymethyl substituent at position 5.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3'R)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B4.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3S)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B3.
A uridine phosphate in which the uridine bears an additional carboxymethyl substituent at position 5 and the phosphono group is at the 5'-oxygen.
A nucleotide residue derived from 5-(carboxymethyl)uridine 5'-monophosphate.
An O-acylcarnitine in which the carnitine component has L-configuration.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3'R)-hydroxy group of (-)-epicatechin-(4alpha->8)-(-)-epicatechin.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of two molecules of (-)-epicatechin joined by a (4alpha->8)-linkage.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3'S)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B3.
A gallate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of gallic acid with the (3S)-hydroxy group of procyanidin B4.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of (+)-gallocatechin and (+)-catechin units joined by a (4alpha->8)-linkage.
An alpha-amino-acid cation obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group and protonation of the amino and guanidino groups of (2S,3R)-capreomycidine.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of (+)-gallocatechin and (-)-epicatechin units joined by a (4alpha->8)-linkage.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of (+)-catechin and (-)-epigallocatechin units joined by a (4alpha->8)-linkage.
A proanthocyanidin consisting of (+)-gallocatechin and (+)-catechin units joined by a (4beta->8)-linkage.
